<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-231-455  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 231 455  OV: 07 231 371.andM; </DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Magazine  Jan 31 1989 v8 n2 p166(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>AST-Ethernet Adaptor. (AST Research Inc.) (Hardware Review)(segment article, one of of 13 evaluations of Ethernet cards)(evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Derfler, Frank J., Jr.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>AST-Research Inc's $595 AST-Ethernet Adapter is a large card thatis expandable and flexible.andP;  The AST-Ethernet Adapter hasconnections for the 16-bit-wide AT bus and allows the user toselect the AT's high numbered IRQ lines to resolve IRQ conflictswith other I-O devices.andP;  The card features 16Kbytes of RAM and canbe upgraded in 16Kbyte increments to 64Kbytes using static RAMchip sets.andP;  A program called Smart Switch is included thatdisplays information about configuration options, and makesconfiguration suggestions.andP;  The installation manual is very good.andO;The AST-Ethernet Adaptor is aimed strictly at the Novellmarketplace.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   AST Research Inc. (products).andO;Ticker:    ASTA.andO;Product:   AST Research Ethernet Adapter (Circuit board).andO;Topic:     Communications Boards-CardsEthernetEvaluationComparison.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>AST RESEARCH AST-ETHERNET ADAPTER The AST-Ethernet Adapter cards are big: wehad to remove the card guides at the end of the expansion slots to get thesecards into our machines.andM;Though large, AST's card is flexible and expandable.andP;  It has connections forthe 16-bit-wide AT bus and allows you to select the AT's high-numbered IRQlines (10, 11, 12, and 15) to resolve IRQ conflicts with other I/O devices.andO;The board comes with 16K of RAM, and you can upgrade it in 16K increments to64K using static RAM chip sets.andP;  (This RAM upgrade is usually required onlyfor a card operating in a very active server.)andM;Instead of forcing you to puzzle over jumpers or DIP switches if you want tochange the factory-configured settings, AST supplies a software programcalled Smart Switch.andP;  Not only does Smart Switch display information aboutyour options, but it also makes configuration suggestions--telling you, forexample, how to put up to four AST-Ethernet cards in the same machine.andM;AST includes a very good installation manual.andP;  The troubleshooting sectioncontains suggestions on how to respond to 16 commonly encountered errormessages.andP;  The maintenance section includes some good hints, though eachsuggestion almost always mentions making sure that the card is properlyinserted and the cables are connected.andM;At $595 the AST-Ethernet Adapter cards are at the high end of the Ethernetcard marketplace.andP;  They are aimed strictly at the Novell marketplace; ASTdoes not supply drivers for NetBIOS or other LAN operating systems.andP;  But ifyou're looking for a good card to put into a server, or if you have a networkof AST Premium PCs, the AST cards are strong contenders.andP;  (If you use thiscard in an AST Premium/286, you should set a parameter that allows it to usespecial hardware in the AST Premium to run without wait states.)andO;</TEXT></DOC>